<br>
It's ironic how so many of these people who are vehement about saving the natural environment demand that space be considered a virgin wilderness and be closed off from  humanity forever.  The radical eco-warriors don't seem to understand that having humanity move into space is the best last hope for life on this planet since we'll have to escape the solar system eventually.  Ultimately, I believe it's possible that we may not only save life from the extinction of the solar system but perhaps from the death of the universe itself if we learn how to create mini-bubble universes or some other exotic escape capability in the very far future.  The human extinctionists though must think the Earth will last for an eternity if we just go poof into the night.  Hell the next ice age that will happen in the next 10,000 years or so could result in the extinction of most higher forms of life.  I think we should get on learning to live in space NOW and not wait until the last minute like some people advocate.   Intelligence is worth preserving.  <br>
